(652, 'Internal: Provide (or attach) an organogram for the laboratory depicting the management structure and the interrelationship of all laboratory staff. External: Provide (or attach) an organizational diagram depicting the relationship of the laboratory within the broader laboratory network.', 'Internal: Provide (or attach) an organogram for the laboratory depicting the management structure and the interrelationship of all laboratory staff. External: Provide (or attach) an organizational diagram depicting the relationship of the laboratory within the broader laboratory network.', '', 'Nội bộ: Cung cấp (hoặc đính kèm) cấu trúc tổ chức cho phòng thí nghiệm mô tả cơ cấu quản lý và mối tương quan của tất cả các nhân viên phòng thí nghiệm. Bên ngoài: Cung cấp (hoặc đính kèm) một sơ đồ tổ chức mô tả mối quan hệ của phòng thí nghiệm trong mạng lưới phòng thí nghiệm rộng lớn hơn.', 'Interne : Tracer (ou joindre) un organigramme du laboratoire présentant la structure de la direction et les liens hiérarchiques existant entre chacun des membres du personnel. Externe : Tracer (ou joindre) un organigramme décrivant les relations du laboratoire avec les autres laboratoires du réseau'),
(653, 'LABORATORY FLOORPLAN & LAYOUT                                                                                           ', 'LABORATORY FLOORPLAN & LAYOUT                                                                                           ', '', 'THIẾT KẾ PHÒNG XÉT NGHIỆM                                                                                           ', 'PLAN ET AMÉNAGEMENT DU LABORATOIRE'),
(654, 'Briefly sketch the general layout of the laboratory (or attach). Include and label all departments, testing areas, and non-testing areas and any applicable designation of PCR testing suite and/or BSL-3 area.', 'Briefly sketch the general layout of the laboratory (or attach). Include and label all departments, testing areas, and non-testing areas and any applicable designation of PCR testing suite and/or BSL-3 area.', '', 'Phác thảo bố trí chung của phòng thí nghiệm (hoặc đính kèm). Bao gồm và dán nhãn tất cả các phòng ban, khu vực xét nghiệm, và các khu vực không xét nghiệm bất kì khu vực nào thiết kế cho PCR và / hoặc khu vực BSL-3.', 'Esquisser (ou joindre) le plan général du laboratoire. Inclure et nommer l’ensemble des services, les zones d’analyse et les zones réservées à un usage autre que les analyses, et indiquer le cas échéant les salles réservées à la PCR et/ou la zone NSB-3.'),
(655, 'PART II: LABORATORY AUDIT', 'PART II: LABORATORY AUDIT', '', 'PHẦN III: ĐÁNH GIÁ PHÒNG XÉT NGHIỆM ', 'PARTIE III : ÉVALUATION DU LABORATOIRE'),
(656, 'Laboratory audits are an effective means to 1) determine if a laboratory is providing accurate and reliable results; 2) determine if the laboratory is well-managed and is adhering to good laboratory practices; and 3) identify areas for improvement.', 'Laboratory audits are an effective means to 1) determine if a laboratory is providing accurate and reliable results; 2) determine if the laboratory is well-managed and is adhering to good laboratory practices; and 3) identify areas for improvement.', '', '', ''),
(657, 'Auditors complete this audit using the methods below to evaluate laboratory operations per checklist items and to document findings in detail.', 'Auditors complete this audit using the methods below to evaluate laboratory operations per checklist items and to document findings in detail.', '', '', ''),
(658, '• Review laboratory records to verify that the laboratory quality manual, policies, personnel files, equipment maintenance records; audit trails, incident reports, logs, Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and other manuals (e.g., safety manual) are complete, current, accurate, and annually reviewed.', '• Review laboratory records to verify that the laboratory quality manual, policies, personnel files, equipment maintenance records; audit trails, incident reports, logs, Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and other manuals (e.g., safety manual) are complete, current, accurate, and annually reviewed.', '', '', ''),
(659, '• Observe laboratory operations to ensure:', '• Observe laboratory operations to ensure:', '', '', ''),
(660, 'o Laboratory testing follows written policies and  procedures in pre-analytic, analytic and post-analytic phases of laboratory testing;', 'o Laboratory testing follows written policies and  procedures in pre-analytic, analytic and post-analytic phases of laboratory testing;', '', '', ''),
(661, 'o Laboratory procedures are appropriate for the testing performed;', 'o Laboratory procedures are appropriate for the testing performed;', '', '', ''),
(662, 'o Deficiencies and nonconformities identified are adequately investigated and resolved within the established timeframe.', 'o Deficiencies and nonconformities identified are adequately investigated and resolved within the established timeframe.', '', '', ''),
(663, '• Ask open-ended questions to clarify documentation seen and observations made. Ask questions like, “show me how…” or “tell me about…” It is often not necessary to ask all the checklist questions verbatim. An experienced auditor can often learn to answer multiple checklist questions through open-ended questions with the laboratory staff.', '• Ask open-ended questions to clarify documentation seen and observations made. Ask questions like, “show me how…” or “tell me about…” It is often not necessary to ask all the checklist questions verbatim. An experienced auditor can often learn to answer multiple checklist questions through open-ended questions with the laboratory staff.', '', '', ''),
(664, '• Follow a specimen through the laboratory from collection through registration, preparation, aliquoting, analyzing, result verification, reporting, printing, and post-analytic handling and storing samples to determine the strength of laboratory systems and operations.', '• Follow a specimen through the laboratory from collection through registration, preparation, aliquoting, analyzing, result verification, reporting, printing, and post-analytic handling and storing samples to determine the strength of laboratory systems and operations.', '', '', ''),
(665, '• Confirm that each result or batch can be traced back to a corresponding internal quality control (IQC) run and that the IQC was passed. Confirm that IQC results are recorded for all IQC runs and reviewed for validation.', '• Confirm that each result or batch can be traced back to a corresponding internal quality control (IQC) run and that the IQC was passed. Confirm that IQC results are recorded for all IQC runs and reviewed for validation.', '', '', ''),
(666, '• Confirm PT results and the results are reviewed and corrective action taken as required. ', '• Confirm PT results and the results are reviewed and corrective action taken as required. ', '', '', ''),
(667, '• Evaluate the quality and efficiency of supporting work areas (e.g., phlebotomy, data registration and reception, messengers, drivers, cleaners, IT, etc).', '• Evaluate the quality and efficiency of supporting work areas (e.g., phlebotomy, data registration and reception, messengers, drivers, cleaners, IT, etc).', '', '', ''),
(668, '• Talk to clinicians to learn the users’ perspective on the laboratory’s performance. Clinicians often are a good source of information regarding the quality and efficiency of the laboratory. Notable findings can be documented in the Summary and Recommendations section at the end of the checklist.', '• Talk to clinicians to learn the users’ perspective on the laboratory’s performance. Clinicians often are a good source of information regarding the quality and efficiency of the laboratory. Notable findings can be documented in the Summary and Recommendations section at the end of the checklist.', '', '', ''),
(669, 'AUDIT SCORING', 'AUDIT SCORING', '', 'CHO ĐIỂM', 'SYSTÈME DE NOTATION'),
(670, 'This   Stepwise Laboratory Improvement Process Towards Accreditation Checklist contains 111 main sections (a total of 334 questions) for a total of 258 points. Each item has been awarded a point value of 2, 3, 4 or 5 points—based upon relative importance and/or complexity. Responses to all questions must be, “yes”, “partial”, or “no”.', 'This   Stepwise Laboratory Improvement Process Towards Accreditation Checklist contains 111 main sections (a total of 334 questions) for a total of 258 points. Each item has been awarded a point value of 2, 3, 4 or 5 points—based upon relative importance and/or complexity. Responses to all questions must be, “yes”, “partial”, or “no”.', '', '', ''),
(671, '0', '', '', '', ''),
(672, 'Items marked “yes” receive the corresponding point value (either 2, 3 or 5 points). All elements of a question must be present in order to indicate “yes” for a given item and thus award the corresponding points.', 'Items marked “yes” receive the corresponding point value (either 2, 3 or 5 points). All elements of a question must be present in order to indicate “yes” for a given item and thus award the corresponding points.', '', 'Mục được trả lời “có” nhận được giá trị điểm tương ứng (2 hoặc 3 hoặc 5 điểm). Tất cả các yếu tố của một câu hỏi cần phải trả lời “có” cho mỗi mục để có điểm thích ứng.', 'Les rubriques pour laquelle la réponse est « oui » se voient attribuer le nombre de points correspondant (2, 3 ou 5 points). Tous les éléments d’une question doivent être présents pour pouvoir répondre « oui » à une rubrique donnée et accorder ainsi les points correspondants.'),
(673, 'NOTE: items that include “tick lists” must receive all “yes” and/or “n/a” responses to be marked “yes” for the overarching item.', 'NOTE: items that include “tick lists” must receive all “yes” and/or “n/a” responses to be marked “yes” for the overarching item.', '', 'LƯU Ý: Những yếu tố trong một mục có hệ thống đánh dấu phải nhận tất cả câu trả lời “có” và/hoặc “không áp dụng” để được kết luận là “có” cho toàn mục đó.', 'N.B.: Pour les rubriques constituées de « listes à cocher », il convient de répondre « oui » et/ou « n/a » partout pour pouvoir répondre « oui » à la rubrique entière.'),
(674, 'Items marked “partial” receive 1 point. ', 'Items marked “partial” receive 1 point. ', '', 'Mục được đánh dấu “một phần” nhận được 1 điểm.', 'Les rubriques pour lesquelles la réponse est « partiellement » reçoivent 1 point. '),
(675, 'Items marked “no” receive 0 points. ', 'Items marked “no” receive 0 points. ', '', 'Mục được đánh dấu “không” nhận được 0 điểm', 'Les rubriques pour lesquelles la réponse est « non » ne reçoivent aucun point. '),
(676, 'When marking “partial” or “no”, notes should be written in the comments field to explaining why the laboratory did not fulfill this item to assist the laboratory with addressing these areas of identified need following the audit.', 'When marking “partial” or “no”, notes should be written in the comments field to explaining why the laboratory did not fulfill this item to assist the laboratory with addressing these areas of identified need following the audit.', '', 'Khi trả lời “một phần” hoặc “không”, cần nêu ý kiến trong phần nhận xét để giải thích tại sao phòng xét nghiệm không đạt mục đó để hỗ trợ cho phòng thí nghiệm xác định được phần cần thiết phải cải tiến sau đánh giá. ', 'Lorsque la réponse est « partiellement » ou « non », il convient de détailler dans la zone de commentaires les raisons pour lesquelles le laboratoire ne remplit pas les conditions de cette rubrique, afin d’aider le laboratoire à prendre en charge les domaines dans lesquels des besoins ont été identifiés dans le cadre de l’évaluation.'),
